(1, '1665965d-df7a-47ab-98b6-95883be5be13', 'GHANA ARMED FORCES COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE HOLDS ITS 18TH MATRICULATION CEREMONY', 'ghana-armed-forces-command-and-staff-college-holds-its-18th-matriculation-ceremony', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) held its 18</span><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; height: 0px; line-height: 1; position: relative; bottom: 0.8em; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">th</sup><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">&nbsp;matriculation ceremony for fresh students of the Master of Science in Defence and International Politics Program (MDIP) on Friday 10 March 2023 at the Hamidu Hall of the College, Teshie. The matriculation ceremony was the 10</span><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; height: 0px; line-height: 1; position: relative; bottom: 0.8em; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">th</sup><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">&nbsp;for the weekend programme and the 18</span><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; height: 0px; line-height: 1; position: relative; bottom: 0.8em; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">th</sup><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\"> in total for the College.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">The Commandant of the College, Major General Irvine Nii Ayitey Aryeetey in his welcome address acknowledged the immense contributions of the Legon Centre for International Affairs, the University of Ghana, and the Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration (GIMPA) that have enabled the College to acquire both institutional and program accreditation. He specifically appreciated GIMPA for their constant support and mentorship of the MDIP program.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">The Commandant also indicated that, beyond offering higher military education, the programs run in the College have gone through an extensive transformation, culminating in the introduction of the weekend Master of Science Degree program. He celebrated the hard work and achievements of the Dean of the Academic Division, Dr. Vladimir Antwi-Danso, the Staff College Control Board, other visionary Generals, as well as past and present members of the College Community.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">He added that national and global insecurity had been aggravated by the rise in activities of non-state actors such as terrorists thereby, making the knowledge and exposure the students were about to acquire very importantly. He, therefore, admonished them to apply themselves to ensure global peace and security. He further added that the College would equip the students with its core values such as honesty, integrity, and dedication to guide them towards successful completion of the course.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">The Deputy Rector of GIMPA, Professor Martin Morgan Tuuli who spoke on behalf of the Rector as the Guest of Honour, urged the Matriculants not to short-change their education, which he described as the commodity for comfort. &ldquo;It has been observed that education is the only commodity which when people are short-changed, are happy&rsquo;&rsquo;, he lamented. Professor Morgan Tuuli also urged the students to work hard and adhere to the directives of the College. This he said, would help prepare them to emerge as leaders at various levels who would contribute their quota to both national and global security.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">Senior Research Fellow and Acting Vice Dean of the college, Dr. Napoleon Kurantin in his note of assurance, encouraged the students to dedicate themselves to their studies since there were no shortcuts at the college. He assured them that the time they will spend in the College holds the key to graduating with the requisite knowledge, skills, confidence, and aptitude to contribute meaningfully to the fortunes of their communities, the world, and humanity at large.</span></p>', 1, '2023-09-13 17:31:16', '2023-09-13 15:09:11'),
(2, '4f234500-d7b5-48ae-912d-3bc74c2c5dad', 'BOTSWANA DEFENCE FORCE COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE DELEGATION EMBARKS ON A BENCHMARKING EXERCISE AT GAFCSC', 'botswana-defence-force-command-and-staff-college-delegation-embarks-on-a-benchmarking-exercise-at-gafcsc', NULL, 'MAJ AMARTEFIO (DDCA GAFCSC)', NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">A 4-man delegation led by Brig Gen Anderson Matlho, from the Botswana Defence Force Command and Staff College, carried out a benchmarking exercise at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) from Monday 15 May to Friday 19 May 2023.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The visit was aimed at exploring collaboration models, joint accreditation of learning programmes, awards of certificates, College structures, quality assurance structures and oversight bodies among others. This was in line with the intention to introduce a Master of Arts in Defence and Strategic Studies at the Botswana Defence Force Command and Staff College.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">As part of the exercise, the delegation interacted with the Commandant and key appointment holders of GAFCSC. They were apprised of the overview of GAFCSC, its academic reforms, administrative challenges, and future strategic plan. Also, there were discussions on curriculum development and a conducted tour of the various facilities in the College.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The delegation also visited the Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration (GIMPA), where they conferred with the Rector and management on the school&rsquo;s relationship with GAFCSC, especially in the area of capacity building.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Additionally, they called on the Director-General and management of the Ghana Tertiary Education Commission (GTEC) and had discussions bordering on quality assurance, accreditation and capacity building.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Other places visited to discuss issues pertaining to the benchmarking exercise were the Kofi Annan International Peacekeeping Training Center (KAIPTC) and the General Headquarters of the Ghana Armed Forces, Burma camp.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Brig Gen Anderson Matlho on behalf of the delegation, expressed his profound gratitude to the Military High Command as well as the Commandant and staff of GAFCSC for hosting them and facilitating the successful conduct of their benchmarking exercise. He also gave an assurance of Botswana&rsquo;s continuous collaboration with GAFCSC and the Ghana Armed Forces in general.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Other members of the delegation were Col Segolame Sebenyane, the Commandant of the Botswana Defence Force Command and Staff College, Professor Rebecca Lekoko, Dean of the College and Dr Kebapetse Lotshwao, Head of Department, University of Botswana.</p>', 1, '2023-09-15 15:11:20', '2023-09-15 15:11:20'),
(3, '7b4c1a34-aeb0-4228-bfac-47424570d80b', 'GAFCSC ENDS PEACE OPERATION COURSE 2023', 'gafcsc-ends-peace-operation-course-2023', NULL, 'MAJ AMARTEFIO (DDCA GAFCSC)', NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">This year&rsquo;s Peace Operations Course (POC) successfully ended at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday, 2 June 2023. The 2-week course was aimed at creating a platform for professional and key personalities with diverse exposure to peace operations to share their experience with participants. It also sought to expose the participants to a critical understanding of the concept and practice of peace operations in an international setting.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">At the closing ceremony, Brigadier General Daniel Frimpong (Rtd) who was the Guest of Honour, stressed the importance of such realistic practical training, as part of the overall capacity-building strategy for peace operations. He pointed out that the changing nature of armed conflicts across the globe required that the planning and execution of activities within Peace support theatres should be done jointly and in an integrated manner. He further explained that the course would help the participants to appreciate the nature and evolution of peace operations in response to the changing conflict dynamics in contemporary times and would also help to draw their attention to command, staff, and leadership challenges in the field.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Brig Gen Frimpong (Rtd) expressed his belief that participants would grow together into a generation of leaders who are well-equipped and positioned to be able to handle the challenges of peace operations since the course afforded them the opportunity to engage with the best in the field and tap from their experience.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The Peace Operations Course is one of the modules organized under GAFCSC&rsquo;s Master of Science Degree in Defence and International Politics (MDIP). Participants of this year&rsquo;s course included 85 regular students of the Senior Division, made up of 61 Ghanaian officers and 24 officers from 11 allied African countries. There were also 13 students from the MDIP weekend class and 13 external participants from other Security Services, Governmental Agencies, and some Media houses in Ghana.</p>', 1, '2023-09-15 15:13:27', '2023-09-15 15:13:27'),
(4, 'bb146291-f1bc-4ec2-85f7-3d9b1dbc9887', 'GHANA ARMED FORCES COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE HOLDS GRADUATION FOR JUNIOR STAFF COURSE 79', 'ghana-armed-forces-command-and-staff-college-holds-graduation-for-junior-staff-course-79', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday 30 June 2023 held a Graduation Ceremony, for students of Junior Staff Course 79. The Course which commenced on 10 February 2023 was made up of 52 officers from the Ghana Armed Forces, 1 from the Armed Forces of Liberia, 1 from the Gambian Armed Forces, 8 from the Armed Forces of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, and 2 from the Botswana Defence Force.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The Guest of Honour for the ceremony, Colonel Ani Asamoah (Rtd) in his address, emphasized the importance of the course. He indicated that it had afforded the graduands the opportunity to broaden their professional and general outlook on matters of both national and international interest. He further said the course had equipped them with the knowledge and skills essential to help them advance effectively and efficiently in discharging their duties. He, therefore, charged them to uphold the good image of the College at all times by applying the knowledge and expertise acquired during the course.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Col Asamoah (Rtd) expressed his delight about the participation and provision of assistance by sister Security Services during the 2-week Internal Security and Counter-insurgency package of the course.&nbsp; He also commended the Commandant, Assistant Commandant, and the staff of GAFCSC for their tireless efforts in achieving such professional excellence.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The Assistant Commandant of the Junior Division, Brigadier General Albert Kwadwo Dawohoso in his course report, stated that as part of the experiential studies package of the College, Junior Staff Course 79 undertook an Environmental Study Tour to the Western Region to conduct research into some of the existing challenges to the development of the Region. He disclosed that the comprehensive reports produced by the students would be forwarded to higher headquarters for appropriate attention.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Brig Gen Dawohoso acknowledged the various forms of assistance rendered to the Junior Division in the areas of training and logistics during the period of the course. He commended the support from all the Departments and Directorates of the General Headquarters, especially from General Headquarters Training and all the training and logistics support units of the Ghana Armed Forces.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Awards were presented to graduands who excelled in various aspects of the course. The Overall Best Student went to Major Anthony Raphael Darko, the second best student to Major Josephson Junior Kwame Odoi, and the third best student to Captain Kingsley Asare Narh. Flight Lieutenant Kolade Temitope Alao of the Nigerian Air Force received the Best Allied Student award.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">For the Assistant Commandant&rsquo;s Research Paper Competition, the best paper went to Captain Kingsley Asare Narh, the second best to Flight Lieutenant Musa Abdullahi Abdulhafiz, and the third best paper to Squadron Leader Ama Serwah. The Everard Award was presented to Maj Stephen Wonoo Addai-Mensah, and the best female student award was presented to Squadron Leader Ameenah Tahiru.</p>', 1, '2023-09-15 15:15:04', '2023-09-15 15:15:04'),
(5, '8032d3d1-d9cf-49ab-a739-53582032fc07', 'GAFCSC CLOSES DEFENCE MANAGEMENT COURSE 2023', 'gafcsc-closes-defence-management-course-2023', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">A brief closing ceremony was held at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday 7 July 2023 to mark the end of the Defence Management Course 2023.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">The 2-week Course was aimed at exposing uniformed and civilian personnel working within the security sector to the issues, principles, and techniques relevant to improving the governance and management of the defence and security sectors. The course consisted of students of Senior Command and Staff Course 44 and external participants drawn from sister Security Services, Ministries, Departments, and Agencies.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">In her closing address, the Vice Chairperson of the Parliamentary Select Committee on Defence and Interior, Honourable (Hon) Ophelia Mensah Hayford who was the Guest of Honour at the ceremony emphasized the crucial nature of the Course. She indicated that Ghana could not downplay the significance of defence and security management in the midst of increasing sophistication and the illusive nature of threats in our part of the world.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">She commended GAFCSC for incorporating innovative programs into its curriculum and for bringing together state agencies to study and find solutions to important national issues. She also applauded the college for implementing practical programs like the Defence Management Course to bridge the gap between theory and practice.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Hon Ophelia Mensa congratulated the course participants for exhibiting exceptional resilience and determination throughout the rigorous program and added that it was a testament to their unwavering dedication to serving their respective nations.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Present at the ceremony were the Commandant GAFCSC Major General Irvine Nii Ayitey Aryeetey, Deputy Commandant Brigadier General Abass Seidu, and other Senior Staff of the College.</p>', 1, '2023-09-15 15:16:14', '2023-09-15 15:16:14'),
(6, 'eff93539-2b68-4bf0-a83d-3eb84809f6ec', 'GAFCSC HOLDS CONFLICT AND CRISIS MANAGEMENT COURSE 2023', 'gafcsc-holds-conflict-and-crisis-management-course-2023', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">As part of the modules organised under the Master of Science in Defence and International Politics, a two-week course on Conflict and Crisis Management Course was held at GAFCSC from 10 to 21 July 2023. The course was aimed at providing a clear understanding of conflict and crisis management to enable participants to work more effectively, efficiently and cohesively.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">During the opening ceremony, the National Security Coordinator, Mr Edward Asomani who was the Guest of Honour, lauded GAFCSC for being one of the leading institutions that run courses and modules that bring together personnel from key national institutions to help achieve the synergy needed for national security and development. He encouraged the participants to ensure that the objectives of the course were well etched on their minds as they go through the course. He added that the objectives would help increase the potential of the various organisations for conflict and crisis management in order to minimize human suffering, loss of lives and properties and ultimately ensure a more resilient, safe, and secure nation.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Mr Asomani also pledged that the Ministry of National Security would sponsor the 2023 Conflict and Crisis Management Course and that of 2024, to facilitate the effective and efficient management of conflicts and crises in the country.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Speaking at the closing ceremony, the Guest of Honour, a Senior Lecturer at the Ghana School of Law, Mr Kwame Gyan commended the participants for their display of dedication throughout the course and charged them to put the knowledge acquired to good use in their various organizations. He stressed that effective collaboration among academia, government institutions and the private sector forms an important connection to the effective management of conflict and crisis, hence the need for collective responsibility.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif;\">Participants of the Course comprised students of the Senior Command and Staff Course 44, weekend students of the Master of Science and International Politics and external participants drawn from other Security Services, Ministries, Departments and Agencies.</p>', 1, '2023-09-15 15:17:44', '2023-09-15 15:17:44'),
(8, 'a3b5f48f-c7ff-4e96-a8a3-1626f6528ba7', 'GAFCSC COMMANDANT WELCOMES STUDENTS OF COURSE 45', 'gafcsc-commandant-welcomes-students-of-course-45', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant, GAFCSC, Major General Irvine Nii-Ayitey Aryeetey, emphasized the importance of diligence and meticulousness to students of the Senior Command and Staff Course 45. He made this assertion during his welcome address on Tuesday, 19 September, 2023, at the Hamidu Hall.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He encouraged the students to conscientiously plan and execute their activities with professionalism and discipline, underlining that effective planning was a crucial element for success in the course. Senior Command and Staff Course 45 assembled on Friday 8 September to commence an 11-month training in leadership, command and staff responsibilities. <a name=\"_Hlk147405010\"></a>The military program is also integrated with some academic programs, namely, Master of Science in Defence and International Politics (MDIP), and Master of Science in Security Studies (MSS). At the end of the academic year, the students will graduate with the Pass Staff Course and MDIP/MSS certificates.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Course is made up of 98 students from the Ghana Armed Forces and the Armed Forces of Benin, Botswana, Burkina Faso, The Gambia,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Guinea, La Cote D&rsquo;Ivoire, Liberia and Malawi. Other countries represented are Namibia, Nigeria, Rwanda, Sierra Leone, South Africa, Tanzania, Togo and Zambia.</span></p>', 1, '2023-10-10 14:21:07', '2023-10-10 17:29:07'),
(9, '774f990a-5809-4ac0-851c-38ce625d0d90', 'MAJ GEN ONWONA TAKES OVER AS COMMANDANT OF GAFCSC', 'maj-gen-onwona-takes-over-as-commandant-of-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">GAFCSC welcomed its 22nd Commandant, Major General (Maj Gen) Bismark Kwasi Onwona, on Friday, 6 October, 2023.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696954988.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The momentous occasion marked the transition of leadership at the prestigious institution, as Maj Gen Irvine Nii-Ayitey Aryeetey handed over to Maj Gen Onwona as the new Commandant. Maj Gen Aryeetey who served a total period of nine months of unblemished and dedicated service at the helm of affairs at GAFCSC, has been appointed as the Commandant of the newly established National College of Defence Studies (NCDS).</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Out-dooring the New Commandant in a durbar, Maj Gen Aryeetey expressed his confidence in Maj Gen Onwona\'s capabilities, urging all personnel to provide the same unwavering support accorded him to the new Commandant. He emphasized the importance of overcoming challenges and raising the standard of excellence that GAFCSC is known for.&nbsp; The Outgoing Commandant commended the dedication of personnel of the College in upholding its distinguished reputation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955019.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">In his brief remarks, Maj Gen Onwona extended his gratitude to his predecessor for the transformative work done during his tenure, which contributed significantly to the College\'s progress. He stressed the need for unity and cooperation among all personnel to help him ensure the fulfilment of GAFCSC\'s vision and mission.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955035.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></span></p>', 1, '2023-10-10 14:35:52', '2023-10-10 17:22:59'),
(10, 'cd0ef5ec-db08-4e57-bcc5-e63d2ac5c612', 'GAFCSC CONDUCTS INDUCTION RELIGIOUS SERVICE FOR STUDENTS OF COURSE 45', 'gafcsc-conducts-induction-religious-service-for-students-of-course-45', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has conducted an Induction Religious Service for students of Senior Command and Staff Course 45 on Sunday, 1 October, 2023, at the Hamidu Hall in Teshie. The purpose of the induction service was to cultivate a profound sense of unity and camaraderie among the students, uniting them in a spiritual and communal ambiance. The induction religious service also underscores the paramount significance of ethical conduct, moral values, and unwavering commitment to principles. These attributes are utmost importance for military personnel who might encounter intricate and morally challenging situations in line with their studies.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696954172.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2572\" height=\"1168\" /><br /><br />The Guest of Honour, Alhaji Iddi Sumaila who is the Chief Executive Officer of Skones Group of Companies, mentioned that the homily by the Imam and the Chaplain on the theme \"Integrity in the Acquisition of Knowledge had stimulated his thoughts and that of the students.<br />He entreated the students to reflect on the theme and well-delivered sermon and allow the admonitions to inspire them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955365.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Emphasizing the aim of the course, the Guest of Honour stressed the need for honesty, integrity, and exceptional performance in their profession. He encouraged the students to focus on developing these qualities in order to excel in their careers.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">He extended his gratitude to the families of the students for their support and welcomed the Allied Officers with warm hospitality, encouraging them to embrace the fraternal relations and enjoy the beauty of Ghana.</span></span></p>', 1, '2023-10-10 14:52:51', '2023-10-10 16:29:30'),
(11, '25b48510-9612-46d9-b824-2fea4bc2a200', 'GAFCSC HOLDS MATRICULATION FOR STUDENTS OF COURSE 45', 'gafcsc-holds-matriculation-for-students-of-course-45', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">GAFCSC on Thursday, 28 September, 2023, held a matriculation ceremony for the 2023/24 Masters programme for Senior Command and Staff Course 45 at the Hamidu Hall.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955534.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The matriculation ceremony signalled the commencement of an 11-month academic journey for 98 students from the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) and the Armed Forces of Benin, Botswana, Burkina Faso, The Gambia, Guinea, La Cote D&rsquo;Ivoire, Liberia and Malawi. Other countries represented are Namibia, Nigeria, Rwanda, Sierra Leone, South Africa, Tanzania, Togo and Zambia.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">This rigorous 11-month programme is designed to equip selected middle and senior-level officers of GAF, other security services, qualified civilians, and officers from friendly armed forces with the skills necessary for command, staff, and leadership roles in joint, combined, and multi-agency operations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1696955547.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1060\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">In an address at the ceremony, Dr.&nbsp; Yaw Appiah- Marfo, a representative of the Rector of the Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration (GIMPA), emphasized that students would be expected to cultivate analytical thinking, strive diligently to acquire critical thinking skills, and adeptly engage in research using various techniques applicable to their coursework.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Dr Appiah-Marfo highlighted the significance of the dissertation as a pivotal component leading to the award of the Master&rsquo;s Degree. He stressed the importance of students contributing substantially to the realm of knowledge through their research endeavours, to address pertinent issues in the domains of security and defence.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The matriculation ceremony was graced by the presence of high-ranking military and civilian dignitaries, including the Commandant GAFCSC, Maj Gen Irvine Nii-Ayittey Aryeetey, Brig Gen WA Seidu (Deputy Commandant, GAFCSC), Dr Napoleon Kurantin (Vice Dean, GAFCSC), Chief Instructors, and Directing Staff, among others.</span></span></p>', 1, '2023-10-10 14:57:08', '2023-10-10 17:27:22');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `uuid`, `title`, `slug`, `sub_title`, `published_by`, `category`, `content`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(12, '22e841b8-7c03-43e7-be01-28089cd69cb6', 'GAFCSC GRADUATES 76 JSC STUDENTS', 'gafcsc-graduates-76-jsc-students', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) held a graduation ceremony for 76 students of Junior Staff Course 80 on Friday, December 15, 2023, at the Hamidu Hall.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The 19-week course brought together students from Ghana and allied countries, aiming to train selected officers in staff functions by developing their leadership, analytical, and communication skills, laying the foundation for their future career development.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1703000915.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"6240\" height=\"3504\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Guest of Honour, Nana Prah Agyensaim VI, the Paramount Chief of Assin Owirenkyi Traditional Area in the Central Region, emphasized in his speech that the course served as a gateway for the graduates to expand their professional knowledge, gaining broader perspectives on national and global affairs. He highlighted that the curriculum was designed to furnish students with vital competencies for junior and mid-level military roles.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Nana Prah mentioned that the insights the students acquired would undoubtedly position them to navigate and address the complex challenges in their career progression. He reminded them of the critical importance of training in a world fraught with threats to peace, ranging from terrorism to natural disasters, charging them that their newfound knowledge and skills were crucial in understanding and mitigating such threats.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Guest of Honour reiterated that the Ghana Armed Forces played a key role in domestic security operations, emphasizing the importance of robust civil-military relations in resolving security challenges. He urged all attendees to be committed to problem-solving, personnel management, and maintaining high standards of discipline and integrity, upholding the esteemed reputation of the institution through the application of the expertise they had acquired.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">As part of their studies, Junior Staff Course 80 conducted an Environmental Study Tour to the Bono and Ahafo Regions. They explored challenges in these regions, covering topics such as protecting forest reserves, addressing illegal small-scale mining, and evaluating waste management efforts. Additionally, they focused on promoting access to quality female STEM education in the Bono Region.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1703001261.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"6240\" height=\"3504\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1703001151.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"6240\" height=\"3504\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">At the end of the course, Major Patrick Peprah Obuobi was adjudged the Overall Best student and Best in Assistant Commandant\'s Paper, while Major Patience Naa Ayorkor Badger was adjudged the Second Best Student, Second Best in Assistant Commandant\'s Paper, and the Best Female Student. Squadron Leader Samuel Gyan Oppong won the Everard Award, while Flight Lieutenant David Dillimono was adjudged the Best Allied Student.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">By Sgt Opoku Solomon</span></p>', 1, '2023-12-19 15:45:56', '2023-12-19 15:54:30'),
(13, '04f62dc4-607b-4c4d-af9d-4b1c42754279', 'MINISTRY OF EDUCATION AND GAFCSC UNITE FOR A FUTURE UNIVERSITY', 'ministry-of-education-and-gafcsc-unite-for-a-future-university', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The Minister for Education, Dr. Yaw Osei Adutwum, in a significant stride towards enhancing the educational landscape in the country led a 28-member delegation on a pivotal visit to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Monday, 22 January 2024 at Otu Barracks in Teshie. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The visit came as a result of a prior invitation extended by the college, seeking collaboration for a comprehensive expansion of their academic programmes.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1706017111.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Welcoming the esteemed delegation, the Commandant of GAFCSC, Major General Bismarck Kwesi Onwonah, expressed gratitude for their visit, highlighting it as a milestone in the college\'s history. He expressed optimism that the visit would help address prevalent academic challenges faced by the institution.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The Commandant\'s remarks were preceded by an informative presentation by the Chief Coordinator, Colonel Maxwell Mantey, which expounded on the college\'s pivotal role, organizational structure, and the challenges it encounters. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Dr Yaw Osei Adutwum, in his remarks, acknowledged the military\'s global role in peace and security, affirming his sector\'s commitment to supporting GAFCSC\'s modernization agenda. He pledged collaborative efforts with the Ministry of Defence to seek Parliamentary approval for the college\'s transition into a university. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The Minister for Education assured that his ministry would bolster GAFCSC\'s capacity by providing essential logistical support to meet its objectives. He further, pledged his support to donate 20 laptop computers to the college.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1706017154.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The Minister was accompanied by the Director General (DG), of Ghana Education Service, Dr Eric Nkansah, the Chief Director (CD) at the ministry, Mrs Maamle Andrews and some other officials from the ministry.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">By Sgt Opoku Solomon</span></p>', 1, '2024-01-23 13:40:12', '2024-01-23 13:44:27'),
(14, '4b0fc878-728b-4b7a-876f-eb49050863f6', 'MAJ GEN ONWONA BIDS FAREWELL TO STAFF AND STUDENTS OF GAFCSC', 'maj-gen-onwona-bids-farewell-to-staff-and-students-of-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Maj Gen Bismarck Kwesi Onwona has bid farewell to staff and students of GAFCSC in a brief ceremony held at the Hamidu Hall on 30 January 2024. This signified the end of his tenure as the Commandant of the College.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1707227434.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"894\" height=\"503\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">In his farewell address, Maj Gen Onwona officially announced his new appointment as Chief of the Army Staff and indicated that an official handing and taking over ceremony would be held when a new Commandant is appointed to oversee the affairs of the College.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">He highlighted his achievements during his tenure, which included technological advancements and infrastructure development. He mentioned ICT projects, projector installations, facility renovations, and the procurement of customized laptops to help solve some administrative challenges. Additionally, he emphasized the ongoing transformation of the college library to foster a conducive learning environment.<a style=\"color: #000000;\" name=\"_Hlk158024586\"></a></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1707227527.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk158024586;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">Maj Gen Onwona</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\"> expressed his confidence in the future success of GAFCSC and urged everyone to remain committed to the College\'s mission.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1707227569.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Immediately after the farewell address, Maj Gen Onwona cut sod for the construction of a modern entrance, as part of his vision to enhance the College\'s appearance.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">By Sgt Opoku Solomon</span></span></p>', 1, '2024-02-06 13:53:29', '2024-02-09 08:30:31'),
(15, 'c43209b6-b745-4e4e-a8c5-30165cf38efe', 'GAFCSC COMMENCES MARITIME SECTOR GOVERNANCE COURSE 2024', 'gafcsc-commences-maritime-sector-governance-course-2024', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has commenced the 2024 Maritime Sector Governance Course, on Monday 12 February, 2024, at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The 5-day course is designed to provide professional maritime practitioners, decision-makers, and stakeholders in the maritime industry with effective governance of the sector. It also aims to manage marine resources, maintain law and order at sea, ensure the safety of navigation and transit through Exclusive Economic Zones (EEZ) protection, and preserve the marine environment.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Delivering his address as the Guest of honour for the opening ceremony, the former Chief Executive Officer of the Ghana Chamber of Bulk Oil Distributors, Mr Senyo Kwasi Hosi, expressed his excitement about the course module. He believed that it would help address the challenges that Ghana is facing in the maritime sector since Ghana\'s territorial waters host many sensitive infrastructure and resources that are key to the socio-economic viability of the country.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1707900618.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Mr Hosi emphasized that efficient and effective management of the maritime sector is a way of protecting a country\'s maritime resources and interests. He added that this could be achieved through the management of marine resources and maintenance of law and order at sea, by preventing illegal activities, as well as ensuring the safety of lives and properties at sea.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">He further explained that the course would ensure a more professional and holistic understanding of Exclusive Economic Zone management and operations by all stakeholders. This, in his view, would engender the political and institutional need to consider decisions affecting the effective and efficient protection of the enormous resources in the zone.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1707900775.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Mr Hosi encouraged the participants to learn to impact society, and not just learn for promotion or certificate, stressing that the course would equip them with the courage to address critical challenges whenever confronted in the maritime domain.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1707900796.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The Maritime Sector Governance Course is one of the various modules organized as part of GAFCSC&rsquo;s Masters programs. The course brought together students of the Senior Command Staff and Course 45, weekend students of GAFCSC&rsquo;s Masters programs, and some external participants drawn from the maritime industry, Ministries, Departments, and Agencies.</span></p>', 1, '2024-02-13 12:15:18', '2024-02-14 08:53:46'),
(16, 'f4a15957-7c35-4f10-bd09-6c9c73503faa', 'STAKEHOLDERS IN THE MARITIME SECTOR URGED TO COMBAT EXPLOITATION AND DISRUPTION', 'stakeholders-in-the-maritime-sector-urged-to-combat-exploitation-and-disruption', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">The Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Dalex Finance and Leasing Company Limited, Mr Kenneth Kwamina Thompson, has urged stakeholders of the Maritime Sector to safeguard the maritime domain from unlawful exploitation. He emphasized this during the closing ceremony of this year&rsquo;s Maritime Sector Governance Course, held at GAFCSC on Friday, 16 February 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Delivering a compelling speech at the ceremony, Mr Thompson who was the Guest of Honour, highlighted the pressing need for concerted efforts to safeguard the maritime sector from individuals and organizations seeking to exploit vulnerabilities for personal gain, to the detriment of countries and the broader sub-region.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">He mentioned that effective and coordinated strategies are essential to ensure sustainable utilization of the maritime enclave and to counter unlawful exploitation. He further underscored the importance of collaboration between institutions like GAFCSC and other maritime-sector industries to address the challenges facing the sector, including armed robbery at sea, piracy, and arms smuggling.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 17.12px; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;\">Again, he urged participants to leverage the lessons, skills, and networks acquired during the course to help counter the rising tide of piracy and other maritime crimes, thereby protecting global interests.</span></p>', 1, '2024-02-22 14:11:29', '2024-02-22 14:14:07'),
(17, '2b528e70-18c5-4a80-9e81-aaeac74d15fc', 'KENYA JOINT COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE DELEGATION VISITS GAFCSC', 'kenya-joint-command-and-staff-college-delegation-visits-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">A 28-member delegation from the Kenya Joint Command and Staff College (JCSC) on Tuesday, 12 March 12, 2024, visited the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College in Teshie.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1710762085.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The delegation led by the Commandant of the College, Major General EM Kinuthia, was on a 5-day study tour in Ghana to explore lessons learned in Strategic Studies, Leadership, Command, and Management modules, and to familiarize themselves with Ghana\'s socio-political, economic, and defense environment. Other delegation members were the Dean of JCSC, 5 Directing Staff, 3 supporting staff and 18 students.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Upon arrival at GAFCSC, they were warmly received by the Deputy Commandant, Brigadier General WA Seidu. The Chief Coordinator, Colonel MO Mantey, briefed the delegation on the aims and objectives of the college, as well as its organizational structure. They were also briefed on GAFCSC&rsquo;s five-year strategic plans to elevate the college to meet international standards.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1710762132.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1710762199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Additionally, the delegation was conducted around the College and allowed to interact with Senior Command and Staff College 45 students.</p>', 1, '2024-03-18 11:44:37', '2024-03-18 11:57:12'),
(18, '97d8562b-5b44-4072-8cf5-18f5c5cd19ef', 'GAFCSC HOLDS 10TH BI-ANNUAL PUBLIC LECTURE', 'gafcsc-holds-10th-bi-annual-public-lecture', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In a bid to shed light on the complexities of African development within the rapidly evolving global context, students of the Senior Command and Staff Course 45 and the Master of Science in International Politics at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College were treated to a thought-provoking public lecture.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The event marked the 10th bi-annual lecture series hosted by the Academic Division of the College on Wednesday 20 March 2024. It aimed at providing different perspectives and resources which could be used as references in assignments and essays to support the ideas and theories of the students.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">A Senior Advisor to the African Union Commissioner, Ambassador William Azumah Awinador-Kanyirige,&nbsp; took center stage as the distinguished speaker for the occasion. With a theme centered on \"Advancing African Development in a Fast-Changing Global Landscape: A Special Focus on the Sahel,\"</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711177558.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ambassador&nbsp; brought his wealth of experience and expertise to the forefront. Against the backdrop of geopolitical shifts and emerging challenges, Ambassador Awinador-Kanyirige underscored the critical importance of addressing the unique socio-economic and security dynamics facing the Sahel region.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711177590.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Drawing from his extensive diplomatic career and deep understanding of African affairs, he articulated a comprehensive framework for sustainable development in the Sahel, emphasizing the need for multi-faceted approaches and regional cooperation</span>.</p>', 1, '2024-03-23 07:06:47', '2024-03-23 07:06:47'),
(19, 'c0d7d30b-f714-46e5-be52-2440f1c4d37c', 'GAFCSC HOLDS 20TH MATRICULATION CEREMONY FOR MDIP AND MSS STUDENTS', 'gafcsc-holds-20th-matriculation-ceremony-for-mdip-and-mss-students', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Academic Division of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has held its 20th matriculation ceremony for students of the Master of Science in Defence and International Politics (MDIP) and Master of Science in Security Studies (MSS) on Friday, March 22, 2024, at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">A total of 36 students, made up of 30 from MDIP and 6 from MSS, officially enrolled in the college to pursue their academic goals.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In his welcome address, the Deputy Commandant of the College, Brig Gen. WA Seidu, entreated matriculants to acknowledge their commitment to higher education, by recognizing the dedication and hard work that had brought them this far, which also symbolizes the birth of a transformative phase in their lives.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711376188.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He pointed out that the journey was both challenging and rewarding, and it was a testament to the student\'s perseverance. He assured the students that the knowledge and skills they had acquired would have a lasting impact on their careers and personal lives.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He also hoped and wished that their partnership with GIMPA would continue with the establishment of the National Defence University (NDU), which would mark the beginning of their autonomous status and journey as one of the colleges under the umbrella of the NDU.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Deputy Rector at the Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration (GIMPA), who was the Guest of Honor for the ceremony, mentioned that pursuing a graduate programme requires a significant investment of time and money. She added that these two could be intimidating and exciting as they inform one\'s long-term professional decision.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711376233.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Dr. Akonnor emphasized the vital importance of zeal, determination, hope, and the cultivation of networks among peers. She underscored the significance of these qualities in navigating the challenges and seizing the opportunities that lie ahead for the graduates.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711376271.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The address concluded with a resounding call to action, inspiring the matriculants to embark on their future endeavours with passion, purpose, and a steadfast commitment to excellenc</span>e.</p>', 1, '2024-03-25 14:19:27', '2024-03-25 14:19:27'),
(20, '61c64ad5-9161-4cd2-8639-3d98e307f59e', 'TANZANIA COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE  STUDENTS VISITS GAFCSC', 'tanzania-command-and-staff-college-students-visits-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\">The Commandant of the Command and Staff College of Tanzania (CSCT) has led a 36-member delegation to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) for an official visit on Tuesday, March 26, 2024.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\">The delegation comprises eight Directing Staff and 27 course participants &nbsp;who were on a one-week study tour to Ghana to gain practical exposure to different military environments, historical sites, and deepen collaboration amongst the two countries. &nbsp;Their visit was anchored on the theme, &lsquo;Regional bloc strategies in addressing security challenges in Africa.&rsquo;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711471525.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\">Upon arrival at GAFCSC, they were warmly received by the Deputy Commandant, Brigadier General WA Seidu. The Chief Coordinator, Colonel MO Mantey, briefed the delegation on the aims and objectives of the college, as well as its organizational structure. They were also briefed on GAFCSC&rsquo;s five-year strategic plans aimed at elevating the college to meet international standards.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1711471561.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\">Additionally, the delegation was conducted around the College and was given the opportunity to interact with students of Senior Command and Staff College 45.</p>', 1, '2024-03-26 16:46:19', '2024-03-26 16:47:52'),
(21, '3363686c-8f05-49ba-b1f8-6bb9be19c745', 'GAFCSC MAKES GIANT STRIDES IN INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT', 'gafcsc-makes-giant-strides-in-infrastructure-development', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College has made giant strides in the development of infrastructure. This was made known by the Chief of the Army Staff, Major General (Maj Gen) Bismarck Kwesi Onwona, in an address to staff and students during a working visit to the College on Thursday, March 28, 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">As the former Commandant with oversight control of GAFCSC, his visit was aimed at inspecting ongoing projects before he formally hands over to the incoming Commandant of the College.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1712142167.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj. Gen. Onwona, during his tenure, initiated numerous projects to foster a conducive environment for both students and staff and ensure efficient administration and optimal learning experiences.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In his presentation, Maj. Gen. Onwona highlighted the introduction of the Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) academic programme as a groundbreaking achievement for the college. He emphasized that the procurement of 130 new books for the college library was to ensure access to the latest information on peacekeeping operations, international relations, and related topics. He added that the installation of some e-resources as well as nine new air conditioning units, represented essential upgrades to the college\'s library facilities, fostering a comfortable and conducive environment for study and research.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1712142195.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The COAS demonstrated his commitment to enhancing the learning experience at the college by investing significantly in information technology. He made mention of an upgrade of the server room, the installation of LED screens and the upgrade of audio-visual equipment at the various lecture halls, the lay-out of Internet Fibre cables, and a network infrastructure upgrade. He added that 110 customized laptops had been purchased for students, and more were expected from the Ministry of Education and the Defence Section of the British Embassy.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj. Gen. Onwona also inspected the progress of some ongoing projects, including the modernization of the entrance gate, which is expected to be completed within the shortest possible time. He also inspected the tiling of the model room and was assured of furnishing the facility with state-of-the-art equipment.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1712142224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The former Commandant extended appreciation to the entire college staff for their dedication and support in realizing these projects. He emphasized the importance of collaborative efforts in achieving the college\'s educational objectives and expressed confidence in the continuous success and growth of the college.</span></p>', 1, '2024-04-03 11:04:11', '2024-04-03 11:04:11'),
(22, 'bcf90b75-1ca9-4a5c-9e7d-ccdcb22f73da', 'MAJ GEN ESSIEN ASSUMES COMMAND AT GAFCSC', 'maj-gen-essien-assumes-command-at-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien has assumed leadership at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), taking over the reins and responsibilities from his predecessor, Maj Gen Bismack Kwesi Onwona.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713280738.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The transition occurred during a brief ceremony on Tuesday, 16 April 2024, at his office in Otu Barracks, Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The in-coming commandant received a comprehensive briefing on the operational, logistical, and administrative aspects of the college from his predecessor.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The ceremony, dignified by the presence of the Chief of Staff (COS) at the General Headquarters, Maj Gen Joseph Price Osei-Owusu, marked a significant milestone in the annals of the college. It featured a quarter guard and a band display, symbolizing the departure of the former commandant and the inauguration of the new leader.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713280831.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"578\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Handing and taking over ceremonies serve as a platform for the outgoing Commanders to bid farewell to officers and staff of the command, while also facilitating the establishment of rapport between the incoming Commanding Officer and the personnel of the command, ensuring a smooth transition of leadership and continuity of operations.</span></p>', 1, '2024-04-16 15:20:44', '2024-04-17 10:58:56'),
(23, '2f9a4591-dad7-4cf4-897c-d2e1c1176b34', 'COMDT GAFCSC EXTENDS WARM WELCOME TO NARC DELEGATION', 'comdt-gafcsc-extends-warm-welcome-to-narc-delegation', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant of Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Maj Gen Matthew Essien has welcomed a 45-Member delegation from the Nigerian Army Resource Centre (NARC), who are currently on a one-week world study tour to Ghana on Wednesday 17 April, 2024 at Otu Barracks, Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The delegation is in Ghana to familiarise themselves with the Socio-Political, Economic and Military Institutions and also foster the spirit of partnership, knowledge exchange between the two esteemed military institutions.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713481326.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Welcoming the delegation, the Commandant underscored the enduring exchange programs between GAFCSC and military institutions in Nigeria, South Africa, and Rwanda, emphasizing the importance of sharing ideas to foster integration and collaboration among nations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He added that the main intention for the cross-fertilization of ideas was to create the needed platforms to facilitate smooth integration. \'To this end, it is our collective responsibility to continue to create these opportunities among our respective countries, to enable senior and middle-level officers and also members of academia to share ideas as well as to contribute their quota on global trends, threats and demands\'. He advised.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713481356.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 16.8667px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant urged the participants to explore the intricate relationship between military leadership strategy and state cohesion, highlighting the profound impact that effective leadership could have on the unity and resilience of a nation.</span></p>', 1, '2024-04-18 23:02:46', '2024-04-18 23:02:46');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `uuid`, `title`, `slug`, `sub_title`, `published_by`, `category`, `content`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(24, '2bde8706-a8b1-4bdb-81df-0e2d0d2255eb', 'RUSSIAN AMBASSADOR CONFERS WITH COMDT GAFCSC', 'russian-ambassador-confers-with-comdt-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ambassador of the Russian Federation to Ghana, HE Sergei Berknikov, embarked on a significant working visit to the Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Maj Gen Matthew Essien, on Monday, 22 April, 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">This visit marked a pivotal moment within the curriculum of the Students of Staff and Command course 45, focusing on \'Global Power Politics: the Russian Perspective and its Impact on Africa.\'</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713872853.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Matthew Essien warmly welcomed the delegation, expressing profound gratitude for Russia\'s enduring positive influence on Ghana.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He enthusiastically embraced the potential for collaboration between Russia and the college, foreseeing enriching academic pursuit.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1713872917.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"548\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Russian Ambassador highlighted Russia\'s strong ties with the college and Ghana. He proposed presenting Russian history to the college, with a focus on World War II. He promised his commitment to the college in the areas of training and academic activities.</span></p>', 1, '2024-04-23 11:49:04', '2024-04-23 11:51:39'),
(25, 'ee2321ea-963e-43ea-b7ea-42a64412531f', 'ZIMBABWEAN DA TO GHANA CALLS ON COMDT GAFCSC', 'zimbabwean-da-to-ghana-calls-on-comdt-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In a diplomatic move aimed at fostering collaboration between Zimbabwe and Ghana, the Zimbabwean Non-Residential Defense Attache (DA) to Ghana, Colonel Philip Kupe, has paid a courtesy call on the Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Maj Gen Matthew Essien, at his office in Teshie on Tuesday, April 23, 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Expressing&nbsp; the purpose of his visit, Col. Kupe disclosed that his visit revolved around a proposal to exchange students and staff members, to enhance the capacity and capabilities of GAFCSC and Zimbabwean Command and Staff College.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1714040417.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"714\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He articulated the importance of the collaboration, emphasizing the mutual benefits it could bring to both Zimbabwe and Ghana in areas such as knowledge sharing, cultural exchange, and the strengthening of ties between the two African nations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant extended a warm welcome to Colonel Kupe, acknowledging the significance of the proposed partnership. He stressed the need for concerted efforts from both countries to realize the objectives of the programme.</span></p>', 1, '2024-04-25 10:20:41', '2024-04-25 10:20:41'),
(27, '290f417d-1ef5-43f3-9ba9-20a782aab376', 'GAFCSC VISIT\'S ANGOLA FOR AFRICA STUDY TOUR 2024', 'gafcsc-visits-angola-for-africa-study-tour-2024', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College arranged a comprehensive African Study Tour, precisely designed to delve into the complex dynamics surrounding the recent surge of military coups across the African continent and its consequential impact on the democratic aspirations of its nations. Spanning five distinct countries, including Angola, Botswana, Kenya, Morocco, and Nigeria, this experiential learning endeavor aimed at equipping participants with a nuanced understanding of regional and international affairs.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In Angola, the delegation, spearheaded by the esteemed Commandant Maj Gen M. Essien, embarked on a multifaceted journey of exploration and enlightenment. The team\'s engagements commenced with diplomatic courtesies, as they paid homage to the Ministry of Defence and the Ghana Embassy. These interactions not only facilitated cross-cultural exchanges but also provided invaluable insights into the political and military landscape of Angola, clarifying the details of its national defense strategies.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716295039.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"708\" /><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716295055.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">An essential aspect of the study tour was the series of enlightening lectures delivered by eminent resource persons from diverse Angola institutions. These scholarly discourses, precisely curated to address relevant themes related to military coups and democratic governance, served as catalysts for robust intellectual exchange and knowledge dissemination. The delegation, comprising both staff and students, benefited immensely from the wealth of expertise and insights shared by the distinguished scholars, further enriching their understanding of the subject matter.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716294073.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716294102.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Furthermore, the delegation was accorded the privilege of visiting esteemed military institutions such as the Angola Armed Forces War College and the Higher Technical Military Institute. At these respected establishments, the delegates were warmly received and provided with comprehensive briefings on the institutions\' historical significance, academic programs, and strategic objectives. Through guided tours and interactive sessions, the delegation gained profound insights into the intricacies of military education, strategic leadership development, and the pivotal role of research in bolstering national defense capabilities.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716294590.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716294670.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beyond academic pursuits, the study tour also offered participants the opportunity to immerse themselves in Angola\'s rich cultural heritage and historical legacy. Visits to iconic landmarks such as the Antonio Agostinho Neto Memorial and the Angolan Military History Museum provided poignant reminders of the nation\'s storied past and its enduring commitment to preserving its heritage. These experiences not only fostered a deeper appreciation for Angola\'s cultural tapestry but also underscored the essential link between military history and the broader fabric of human civilization.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716296004.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716296022.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Moreover, the study tour served as a platform for fostering bilateral ties and diplomatic relations between Ghana and Angola. Through a series of meticulously curated events, including dinners hosted by both the Ghana Ambassador to Angola and their Angolan counterparts had the opportunity to partake in cultural exchanges and engage in meaningful dialogue on matters of mutual interest. These diplomatic endeavors not only strengthened existing bonds of friendship but also laid the foundation for future collaboration and cooperation between the two nations.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716300309.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><img src=\"../../../uploads/1716300343.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" /></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In conclusion, the African Study Tour undertaken by the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College exemplified a holistic approach to experiential learning, seamlessly blending academic inquiry, cultural immersion, and diplomatic engagement. By providing participants with a comprehensive understanding of the complex geopolitical landscape of the African continent, the tour has undoubtedly equipped them with the requisite knowledge and insights to navigate the evolving challenges and opportunities that lie ahead.</p>', 1, '2024-05-21 11:45:39', '2024-05-21 14:05:56'),
(28, '185780ac-5431-493a-9231-3b8c9d78b500', 'GTEC ASSESSES GAFCSC FOR NATIONAL DEFENSE UNIVERSITY CHARTER', 'gtec-assesses-gafcsc-for-national-defense-university-charter', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Tertiary Education Commission (GTEC) visited the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Monday, May 20, 2024 at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The visit, led by Professor Ahmed Jinapor Abdulai, Chairman of the Commission, comes in response to GAFCSC\'s charter institutional application to become a fully-fledged university.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1716299678.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"561\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Professor Abdulai said the rationale for the visit was an initiative to evaluate all military colleges for the establishment of a National Defense University.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The delegation conducted a comprehensive review of the college&rsquo;s academic programmes , facilities, and administrative procedures. They interacted with faculty members and inspected infrastructure to ensure compliance with both national and international standards.</span></p>', 1, '2024-05-21 13:55:03', '2024-05-21 13:55:03'),
(29, 'c544f31c-f505-40aa-967d-fe200e38488f', 'GAFCSC HOLDS MAIDEN MULTI-DOMAIN OPERATIONS MODULE', 'gafcsc-holds-maiden-multi-domain-operations-module', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has launched the inaugural Multi-Domain Operations and Future Warfare module as part of its curriculum for Senior Command and Staff Course 45 on Monday 27 May 2024 at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The module, which included weekend students from the Master of Science in Defence and International Politics programme(MDIP), as well as participants from other security agencies, aimed to introduce new concepts of warfare and modern military operations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1716892486.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">This two-week module was designed to enhance participants\' understanding of Multi-Domain Operations and their importance in contemporary warfare. It also explored factors that contribute to stress in operational commanders, such as high-stakes decision-making, and discussed common psychological challenges faced by these commanders, including decision fatigue and moral injury.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In his welcome address, the Commandant of GAFCSC, Major General(Maj Gen) Matthew Essien, emphasized the module\'s focus on the complexities of Multi-Domain Operations. He highlighted the need to understand the synergies, keystones, and interdependencies among various domains and the importance of integrating them to achieve both operational and strategic objectives.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1716892449.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He revealed that the programme would offer participants the opportunity to engage with subject matter experts, exchange ideas, and foster collaboration with peers dedicated to enhancing military capabilities in an increasingly volatile and interconnected world. He also underscored the critical role of media in the success or failure of modern warfare, noting its significant impact on public perception through battlefield reporting.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1716892512.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant encouraged all participants to approach the sessions with an open mind, a renewed sense of determination, a willingness to learn, and a readiness to challenge conventional wisdom and operational norms. The external participants included members from various security services and media houses.</span></p>', 1, '2024-05-28 10:35:36', '2024-05-28 10:35:36'),
(30, '043dba02-8c78-4516-9775-39f4e28f173e', 'EOCO BOSS URGES CSE 81 STUDENTS TO COMMIT FULLY TO PROBLEM-SOLVING', 'eoco-boss-urges-cse-81-students-to-commit-fully-to-problem-solving', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Executive Director of the Economic and Organized Crime Office (EOCO), Commissioner of Police (COP) Maa Yaa Tiwaa Addo-Danquah, has charged students of Course 81 to be fully committed to problem-solving, particularly in the training of personnel, their administration, and welfare.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">She made the clarion call while addressing Junior Staff Course 81 graduates during their graduation ceremony at the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday, 14 June 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">COP Tiwaa urged them to uphold the tenets of discipline, integrity, and dedication within the Ghana Armed Forces by applying the knowledge and expertise they had acquired during their training. She stated that, as officers, the course would enable them to broaden their professional and general outlook on matters of both national and international interest.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">She expressed optimism that the knowledge gained would put them in a better position to appreciate and effectively manage the multi-dimensional challenges they would face in their careers.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718636325.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Executive Director of EOCO reminded the students of how the world is beset with several threats to peace and security, stemming from terrorism, ethnic and religious disputes, as well as natural, environmental, and human-induced disasters. She, however, appealed to them to constantly strive for a clearer understanding of what it takes to mitigate these threats.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">\'I exhort you, therefore, as professional military officers, to be proactive in your awareness and preparations at all times, to stay ahead of the challenges you might encounter in your future endeavors,&rsquo; she added.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718636245.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Assistant Commandant in charge of the Junior Division, Brigadier General Albert Kwadwo Dawohoso, in his course report, indicated that Junior Staff Course 81 assembled on 26 January 2024, and commenced lectures on 29 January 2024 with 76 students, of which 67 were from the GAF while the remaining 9 were Allied students.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">At the end of the 19-week course, Major Michael Ekpale was adjudged the overall best student, Captain Victor Ngbede and Major Etornam Nuapah were recognized as the best Allied students and recipients of the Everard Award, respectively.</span></p>', 1, '2024-06-17 14:58:58', '2024-06-17 14:58:58'),
(31, '84f1eaa9-5044-4aba-98a1-dcfb70b16bff', 'GAFCSC COMMANDANT HIGHLIGHTS INTEGRATION AS KEY TO FUTURE WARFARE', 'gafcsc-commandant-highlights-integration-as-key-to-future-warfare', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien, has emphasized the importance of agility, innovation, and integration in future warfare.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He highlighted these elements as essential for effective military strategy and operations in the evolving landscape of global conflict during the closing of the 2024 Multi-Domain Operations and Future Warfare Module, held from 27 May to 14&nbsp; June 2024 at the College in Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718649613.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Essien emphasized that adaptability and flexibility are crucial in the face of evolving threats and challenges. He encouraged participants to apply the comprehensive operational approaches discussed and leverage domain strengths to enhance military effectiveness. He charged them to utilize the knowledge gained with diligence and foresight in their future endeavors, believing in their potential to significantly shape the future of warfare.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718649647.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718649688.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"589\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The course brought together participants from Senior Command and Staff Course 45 and various security agencies to explore the complexities of modern warfare, including the fusion of capabilities across land, sea, air, space, and cyberspace. Discussions centered on the strategic implications of operating in a multi-domain environment</span></p>', 1, '2024-06-17 18:41:47', '2024-06-17 18:41:47'),
(32, '087ce217-927f-4b7e-8804-f3ed45aa5906', 'COMDT GAFCSC VISITS CHIEF JUSTICE OF GHANA', 'comdt-gafcsc-visits-chief-justice-of-ghana', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Major General Matthew Essien, visited the Chief Justice of Ghana, Her Ladyship Justice Gertrude Araba Esaaba Torkornoo, at her office in Accra on Thursday, 20 June 2024. The purpose of the visit was to formally invite the Chief Justice to the Republic Day Public Lecture scheduled for July 1, 2024, at the College in Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718991066.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Commandant emphasized that the Chief Justice\'s presence would significantly strengthen the relationship between the two institutions. He also appealed to the Chief Justice to allow some judges to contribute to the College\'s programs, offering valuable legal perspectives to broaden the student\'s learning environment. This interdisciplinary approach would ensure that future military leaders are well-versed in the legal implications of their actions, better preparing them for contemporary and future warfare challenges.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">In her response, Her Ladyship praised the idea of interdisciplinary collaboration, noting that it would greatly benefit both institutions in fulfilling their Constitutional mandates. She assured the Commandant that she would try her best to attend the Public Lecture on the scheduled date.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1718991033.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Commandant was accompanied by the Chief Coordinator, Colonel Maxwell Mantey, and the Chief Instructor, Academic Affairs, Junior Division, Colonel Dominic Boah.</span></p>', 1, '2024-06-21 17:31:28', '2024-06-21 17:31:28'),
(33, '85d0773e-1d69-48db-86d1-3efab34a6d08', 'COMMANDANT OF GAFCSC CALLS ON SPEAKER OF PARLIAMENT', 'commandant-of-gafcsc-calls-on-speaker-of-parliament', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Commandant, Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College, Maj Gen M Essien paid a courtesy call on the Speaker of Parliament on Tue 25 Jun24 at Parliament House in Accra.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Maj Gen Essien stated that the purpose of the visit was to formally invite the Speaker, Right Honourable Alban Bagbin, and members of the House to the College&rsquo;s maiden Republican Day Public lecture.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He mentioned that it would be appropriate for the House to participate in the public lecture with the theme &ldquo;Reflection of the democratic control on the military and the way forward for sustainability\". The Guest Speaker is Mr Francis Poku Esq former Minister for National Security with Amb Josephine Nkrumah and Prof Kwasi Aning as reviewers. Ministers of State and other prominent dignitaries have been invited for this inaugural public lecture.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1719344181.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On behalf of the Speaker, the 2nd Deputy Speaker of Parliament and MP for Fomena, Hon Andrew Asiamah&nbsp; Amoako and his entourage which is comprised of honorable James Agalga, Mr. Anthony Agyekum, Mrs Janet Frimpong, Mr Sebastian David Damoah, and Madam Margaret Ampah welcomed and expressed his gratitude to Commandant and his delegation, Air Cdre TN Okai, Col M Mantey and Col D Buah on the courtesy call.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1719344214.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Hon Andrew Asiamah Amoako applauded the College for coming up with this good initiative that touches on democracy and the public lecture will help change the perception that Ghanaians have about the military.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He commended the Ghana Armed Forces for adhering to the Constitution.</p>\n<p>He further promised that Parliamentarians would honor the invitation for the Public lecture.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2024-06-25 19:38:26', '2024-06-27 13:15:53'),
(34, 'f8b83903-3941-407e-86bc-c732ec7728a0', 'COMMANDANT GAFCSC VISITS COUNCIL OF STATE CHAIRMAN', 'commandant-gafcsc-visits-council-of-state-chairman', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien paid a visit to the Council of State Chairman, Nana Otuo Siriboe II, on Wednesday, 26 June 2024, at the Accra International Conference Center in Accra.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719493812.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Maj Gen Essien, in his address, gave a brief history of the college and some of its courses. He also stated the purpose of his visit, which was to formally invite the chairman and members of the Council of State to attend the College\'s maiden Republican Day Public Lecture, scheduled for Monday, 1 July 2024.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He mentioned that the public lecture, themed \"Reflections on democratic control over the military and the way forward for sustainability,\" would feature Mr. Francis Poku Esq, former Minister for National Security, as the guest speaker, along with Ambassador Josephine Nkrumah and Prof Kwasi Aning as reviewers.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Commandant emphasized that the public lecture would strengthen the relationship between the military and civilians and promised to work towards making the lecture an annual event, with the possibility of rotating it to other regions at military barracks to involve personnel and civilians.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Nana Otuo Siriboe II, in his remarks, expressed gratitude to the Commandant and his entourage for the visit and assured them that the meeting would be an interactive session on issues such as misinformation and indiscipline, that affect the country.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719493890.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Nana Siriboe II suggested that the Commandant consider moving the lecture day to a date that would be celebrated and remembered by military personnel who fought in World War II, emphasizing the \'Poppy Day\'.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719493919.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He further suggested that the Lecture Day be instituted to immortalize the first Ghanaian Chief of the Defense Staff, Major General Stephen J A Otu. He also urged the Commandant to consider collaborations and to organize the lecture day periodically and rotate it to other regions at military barracks to involve personnel and civilians.</p>', 1, '2024-06-27 13:12:14', '2024-06-27 13:12:14'),
(35, 'a84f6cd8-3940-4e61-8b04-92fb534da3f3', 'GAFCSC COMMANDANT PAYS COURTESY CALLS ON RCOA', 'gafcsc-commandant-pays-courtesy-calls-on-rcoa', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien paid a courtesy call to the Retired Commissioned Officers Association (RCOA) on Thursday, 27 June 2024.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Essien outlined programs offered by the College and extended an official invitation to the RCOA to attend the maiden Republican Day Public Lecture on 1 July 2024. &nbsp;He stated that the lecture, themed, \"Reflections on Democratic Control over the Military and the Way Forward for Sustainability.\" will feature former Minister for National Security, Mr Francis Poku Esq as the Guest Speaker.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719921144.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Essien announced the introduction of a PhD program in Defense and International Politics at the College and sought the Association\'s expertise and experience to enrich the program. He also highlighted the College\'s focus on modernizing its curriculum, including the introduction of Multi-Domain Operations, and emphasized the need for collaboration between the College and RCOA.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719921181.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719921211.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The President of RCOA, Brigadier General Samuel Yanyi-Akofur (Rtd), congratulated Maj Gen Essien on his appointment and praised the College\'s initiative to engage with the Association. He expressed enthusiasm for the PhD program and requested greater involvement in the College\'s exercises and supervision of Officers and Directing Staff.</span></p>', 1, '2024-07-02 11:53:42', '2024-07-02 11:53:42'),
(36, '7672e140-cdb7-4c44-9a25-3447f6c52382', 'GAFCSC LAUNCHES MAIDEN PUBLIC LECTURE', 'gafcsc-launches-maiden-public-lecture', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has launched its maiden Republic Day Public Lecture in partnership with One Ghana Movement. The lecture, themed \"Reflections on </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">D</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">emocratic </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">C</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">ontrol </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">O</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">ver the </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">M</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">ilitary: A </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">W</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">ay </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">orward for </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">S</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">ustainability\", was held on Monday, 1 July 2024, at the Hamidu Hall in Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The event featured the Minister for Defence, Honorable</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> (</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Hon</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">) </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Dominic Nitiwul, as the chairman, former Minister for National Security, Mr Francis Poku Esq, as the principal speaker, Ambassador Josephine Nkrumah, and Professor Kwasi Aning as review lecturers. The lecture aimed to improve professional knowledge, leadership, and communication skills, and to strengthen Civil-Military Cooperation (CIMIC).</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922427.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922142.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922229.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Hon Dominic Nitiwul emphasized the need for democratic oversight of the military, effective inter-agency coordination, and modernization of the military to ensure national security and development. He commended the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) for its professionalism and stressed the need for its personnel to be employed in banks and state institutions after retirement.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Commandant, GAFCSC, Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien, expressed gratitude to the distinguished speakers for sharing their knowledge and insight on the Public Lecture. He also extended his heartfelt </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">appreciation</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> to One Ghana Movement for partnering and establishing an enduring working relationship to benefit GAF.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922309.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922376.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Essien mentioned that the lecture was to explore ways of democratic oversight of the military, strengthen and sustain them for the good of the nation and the people. He emphasized that the engagement would help reflect on crucial issues on how to build military effectiveness, operations, values, and principles to achieve sustainable peace and security and to exchange ideas that transcend disciplinary boundaries to inspire creative thinking.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1719922339.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12pt 0cm 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In a PowerPoint presentation, the former Minister for National Security, Mr. Francis Poku Esq, mentioned that the emerging threats to national security, such as internal conflicts, corruption, youth unemployment, and maritime crimes, require effective inter-agency coordination and collaboration with other security services to curb these threats. He also highlighted that the democratic control of the military and the need for the rule of law are necessary to ensure human rights and security. He stated that the roles of the military are focused on peace and security, and he entreated the government to provide resources for the modernization of the military and also for the military to consider investing in agriculture and infrastructure </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">growth</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> to assist national development.</span></p>', 1, '2024-07-02 12:14:07', '2024-07-03 09:32:03');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `uuid`, `title`, `slug`, `sub_title`, `published_by`, `category`, `content`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(37, 'f8185578-3736-4039-b320-aff8345c2cb8', 'GAFCSC OPENS CCMC 1/2024', 'gafcsc-opens-ccmc-12024', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has opened its Conflict and Crisis Management Course (CCMC) 1/2024 academic year for Senior Command and Staff Course 45 on Monday, 15 July 2024, at the Hamidu Hall, Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">The course aims to provide participants with a comprehensive understanding of conflict and internal crisis management, enabling them to work more effectively, efficiently, cohesively.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1721228344.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">The Guest of Honor and National Security Coordinator, Mr Edward Asomani, in his remarks applauded the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) and GAFCSC for positioning itself as leading institutions offering courses and modules that bring together personnel from key national institutions to foster synergy, urgently needed for national security and development. He expressed delight in being a key stakeholder in national security, sponsoring this year\'s program. He also appreciated </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">Commandant GAFCSC, Major General Matthew Essien for honouring him as the Guest of Honor.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">Mr Edward Asomani emphasized the importance of involving participants from other security services, media houses, and the private sector across the country in building cohesion and purpose between GAF and other institutions, vital for national growth and development.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1721228385.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">Mr Asomani reminded participants of their service as middle-level managers, and the crucial link they create between policymakers and beneficiaries of policy decisions. He stressed that in-depth knowledge, expertise, and professionalism are indispensable in the effective management of conflict and crisis.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">The National Security Coordinator cautioned that poorly managed conflict and crisis threatens the security of existence, and participants should ensure that core objectives are firmly embedded in their minds as they progress. He added that this will enhance the country\'s capabilities in conflict and crisis management, minimizing loss of lives and property.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #252525;\">The Guest of Honour urged participants to bring their rich experiences to bear during simulation exercises, engage meaningfully to enhance and deepen their knowledge for the benefit of their respective countries. He encouraged them to build networks and professional connections that will become valuable resources in times of conflict and crisis.</span></p>', 1, '2024-07-17 15:00:29', '2024-07-17 15:00:29'),
(38, 'e8eb9b2a-9524-4baa-b417-34a3c19fca34', 'CDS VISITS GAFCSC', 'cds-visits-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS), Lieutenant General (Lt Gen) Thomas Oppong-Peprah, has paid a visit to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Thursday, 18 July, 2024, at Teshie Ridge.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">As part of the visit, the CDS toured the college and was briefed on the challenges facing the college, including logistical, training, administrative, and operational matters. He also interacted with personnel of the college.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1721391058.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Commandant of GAFCSC, Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien, congratulated the CDS on his elevation to the highest rank and appointment in the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) and expressed delight for the visit.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Maj Gen Essien stated that the visit was significant in strengthening the bonds between the leadership of GAF and the college, which would shape the minds and capabilities of personnel. He noted that the presence of the CDS would serve as a testament to the values GAF places on education, training, and professional development of the Armed Forces.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He further stated that the visit would provide an opportunity to engage in meaningful discussions, exchange ideas, and explore other avenues for further collaboration and synergy between the operational and educational realms of GAF.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1721391106.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Lieutenant General Thomas Oppong-Peprah applauded the Commandant for his efforts in addressing some of the challenges and expressed his pleasure with the project undertaken to improve the facilities of the college.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The CDS pledged support from the General Headquarters to provide the requisite resources to the college and promised to appeal to the Control Board to augment the college\'s efforts. He also instructed that an ambulance vehicle be donated to the GAFCSC Regimental Aid Post and some vehicles to augment the old vehicles.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1721391138.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Lt Gen Oppong-Peprah encouraged personnel to work as a team, stating that teamwork can tackle challenges and has been crucial to the expansion of GAF. He advised all personnel to bury their differences and stay professional, educating themselves to acquire knowledge that would be impactful and beneficial to mankind as leaders.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He further stated that GAF recognizes the extra hours and effort and that it is imperative to reward personnel for going beyond certain periods of time. He appreciated the Directing Staff for helping personnel acquire the necessary knowledge and professionalism to contribute to the maintenance of peace and security in the country and the world at large.</p>', 1, '2024-07-19 12:12:38', '2024-07-19 12:12:38'),
(39, 'fe0ee411-2919-43d6-990b-b679953202de', 'GAFCSC CLOSES CCMC 1/2024', 'gafcsc-closes-ccmc-12024', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has held a closing ceremony for its Conflict and Crisis Management Course (CCMC) 1/2024 academic year for the Senior Command and Staff Course 45 on Friday, 26 July 2024 at the Hamidu Hall, Teshie Ridge.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The two-week course aimed to provide participants with a comprehensive understanding of conflict and internal crisis management, enabling them to work more effectively, efficiently, and cohesively.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1722374920.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Guest of Honour and Chairman of the National Peace Council, Reverend Doctor (Rev Dr) Ernest Adu-Gyamfi in his remarks thanked the GAFCSC Commandant, Major General Matthew Essien for supporting and contributing in diverse ways to the success of the course. He applauded the college for the innovative programs and the involvement of state agencies to study, deliberate, and seek ways to address national issues.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Rev Dr Ernest Adu-Gyamfi mentioned that the course was organized importantly to understand the various organizational roles and to expose personnel working in various security sectors to use principles and techniques for the management of conflict as well as crisis when the need arises adding that training in the management of conflict and crises is a critical requirement for every nation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1722374959.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He commended the college for the initiative, effective collaboration, and engagement with other security stakeholders. It is exemplary for other academic institutions to develop and run practical programs such as conflict and crisis management and upgrade the skills of the Ghanaian workforce in addressing current or future conflict crises.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1722375003.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Guest of Honour urged all participants to serve as trainers in their various organizations to enable people to benefit from the knowledge acquired. He implored them to make a difference, and impact conflict and crisis management issues.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">He encouraged participants to exchange information regularly and establish links that would improve collaboration between their Agencies for healthier management of future conflict and crisis.</span></p>', 1, '2024-07-30 21:30:17', '2024-07-30 21:34:19'),
(40, '0f853f15-c475-4eea-8fcf-3a3bc37c3e98', 'GAFCSC ENDS CT/ CIED COURSE 2024', 'gafcsc-ends-ct-cied-course-2024', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has climaxed its two-day Counter Terrorism/Counter Improvised Explosive Device (CT/CIED) Course 2024. The Course was organized from Monday 29 to Tuesday 30 July 2024 at the College for students of Senior Command and Staff Course 45 and external participants from sister security agencies.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1722432823.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Course was aimed at training and improving the understanding of officers at the operational level in a joint, multi-national/interagency planning to appropriately deal with violent extremism and terrorist situations. Resource persons for the Course were subject matter experts drawn from the field and academia.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../../uploads/1722433158.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien, the Guest of Honour and Commandant of the College, in his closing remarks, expressed his deep gratitude to the Directing Staff, resource persons, and all for contributing to the success of the Course.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He emphasized that the fight against terrorism and the threat of improvised explosive device requires constant vigilance, adaptability, and a united front.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He also urged all participants to remain committed and apply the lessons learned from the Course. He further eulogised the participants for their cooperation and hard work throughout the programme.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1722432873.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Highlights of the Course included Improvise Explosive Devices/Detection Techniques, Combating Terrorism in the Sub-Region using Kinetic and Non-Kinetic Approaches, Role of the Police in CT and Countering Violent Extremist(s). The Course activities were concluded with a Seminar.</p>', 1, '2024-07-31 13:34:43', '2024-07-31 13:39:46'),
(41, '83e6554b-860f-4a85-9fac-2d3dc260a828', 'LEDZOKUKU MP DONATES TO GAFCSC', 'ledzokuku-mp-donates-to-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Member of Parliament (MP) for Ledzokuku Constituency Hon Benjamin Narteh Ayiku has donated 40 pieces of streetlights to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFSCC) on Tuesday, 6 August 2024.</p>\n<p>The donation forms part of the member of parliament&rsquo;s developmental efforts for the constituency as well as to strengthen ties with the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1723052827.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In a brief ceremony to hand over the streetlights to the college, Hon. Benjamin Ayiku said the streetlights are supposed to augment and improve the lighting system on the premises, to enhance visibility and security. He assured the college of his continuous support as part of his vision to bring development to institutions within the constituency.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1723052866.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Commandant of the College, Major General Matthew Essien expressed gratitude to the MP for his generous act. Wishing the MP a belated birthday, the commandant asked for God&rsquo;s blessings and a brighter future where GAF will continue to work together with other state institutions for the peace and security of the country.</p>', 1, '2024-08-07 17:48:07', '2024-08-07 18:03:00'),
(42, '2bef9549-d14b-4e3a-b685-3ba1c666c295', 'GAFCSC SENIOR  COURSE 45 STUDENTS END EX NKABOM', 'gafcsc-senior-course-45-students-end-ex-nkabom', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) Senior Course 45 students have concluded Exercise NKABOM 2024. The Exercise took place from Wednesday 31 July to Friday 9 August 2024 at the College in Teshie.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong><img src=\"../../uploads/1723572947.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"666\" /></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong><img src=\"../../uploads/1723573021.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"666\" /></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The exercise was aimed at exploring the full gamut of contemporary warfare, which spans a multi-domain environment. It presented a realistic framework that demonstrated the challenges that confronts a Joint All Domain Task Force at both Operational and Tactical levels of warfare.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723573043.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"666\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723573108.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"666\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">During the exercise, students employed various concepts of warfare to plan and conduct a joint all domain and integrated multinational campaign. Students knowledge in Counter Terrorism, Cybersecurity Operations, Peace Enforcement and Media Operations among others were applied.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2024-08-13 18:18:46', '2024-08-13 18:18:46'),
(43, 'd8f52b64-d889-4d6a-954c-e0c29759ebd9', 'SUN ELECTRONICS LIMITED DONATES ELECTRONIC GADGETS TO GAFCSC', 'sun-electronics-limited-donates-electronic-gadgets-to-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Sun Electronics Limited, distributors of Hisense products in Ghana, has donated assorted electronic gadgets to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday, 9 August 2024,&nbsp; in Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The donation, presented by a team member from the Corporate Sales Department, Madam Hinanit Opoku included television sets and refrigerators. The items were received by the Commandant of GAFCSC, Major General Matthew Essien.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723574247.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723574295.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">According to Madam Opoku, the CEO of Sun Electronics Limited, Mr Amadu Yahaya has also promised to provide interactive boards for &nbsp;the college\'s lecture halls in the future.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Major General Essien expressed gratitude for the donation, acknowledging the existing partnership between Hisense Ghana and the Ghana Armed Forces. He hoped that the donation would mark the beginning of a fruitful collaboration between GAFCSC and Sun Electronics Limited.</span></p>', 1, '2024-08-13 18:39:24', '2024-08-13 18:39:24'),
(44, 'd0614205-e411-4c29-82ac-35df86d50fc8', 'GAFCCEH INTERACTS WITH STUDENTS OF SCSC 45', 'gafcceh-interacts-with-students-of-scsc-45', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Critical Care and Emergency Hospital (GAFCCEH) held an interactive forum with students of Senior Command and Staff Course (SCSC) 45 at the Hamidu Hall in Teshie on Monday, 12 August 2024. The engagement aimed to update the students on the hospital\'s progress towards operationalization and highlight outstanding issues and future projections.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">The GAFCCEH Administrative Officer Lieutenant Colonel Richard Okyere Mintah, in a presentation revealed that the hospital was established by the United Nations (UN) as a UN COVID-19 Field Hospital (UNCF) pursuant with a Memorandum&nbsp; of Understanding signed in September 2020 and handed over to the Ghanaian government in February 2023.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723575892.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He again highlighted the hospital\'s vision, mission, organizational structure, and operationalization roadmap, as well as developments in the surgical unit, theater, and ongoing projects, including the enhancement of the dialysis waiting room by Ghana Commercial Bank.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1723575914.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">He discussed some outstanding issues including the expansion of the dialysis unit, bus shuttle system, and accommodation.</p>', 1, '2024-08-13 19:05:31', '2024-08-13 19:05:31'),
(45, '3b982110-514b-420d-8f34-9868238275d6', 'GAFCSC COMMANDANT VISITS FHUC', 'gafcsc-commandant-visits-fhuc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) Major General Matthew Essien, has paid a visit to the Family Health University College (FHUC) on Tuesday 13 August 2024.</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Leading a four-member delegation to the health institution, the commandant extended an official invitation to the graduation ceremony of Senior Command and Staff Course 45.</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">In an interaction with President of FHUC, Maj Gen Essien expressed gratitude to the hospital for their warm reception and extended an official invitation to the Senior Command and Staff Course 45 graduation ceremony, scheduled for Friday, August 23, 2024.</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">He seized the opportunity to inform them about the various master\'s and PhD programs offered at the college, encouraging their participation to enhance and strengthen the cordial relationship between both institutions.</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">In his remarks, the President of the University, Prof. Enyonam Kwawukume, expressed gratitude to the delegation for their significant and noteworthy visit. He praised the college for its dedication to professionalism suggesting that if other institutions in the country could replicate the level of discipline instilled by GAFCSC, it would greatly enhance discipline across the country.</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Registrar of the University Mrs. Rita Kaine highlighted some programs offered, including Basic Midwifery and Nursing. She encouraged soldiers with relevant qualifications to consider enrolling in these programs.</span></p>', 0, '2024-08-14 14:34:11', '2024-08-14 14:50:38'),
(46, 'ce0a424f-dc15-415b-977b-250f019e0f8e', 'GAFCSC SENIOR COMMAND AND STAFF COURSE 45 REGIMENTAL  DINNER HELD', 'gafcsc-senior-command-and-staff-course-45-regimental-dinner-held', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) Course 45 has held a dinner night on Friday, 17 August 2024 at Teshie, Accra. The regimental dinner was in honour of the Senior Command and Staff Graduating Course 45.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guest of Honour for the occasion Lieutenant General (Lt Gen) Peter Augustine Blay(Rtd) in his speech expressed his deep appreciation to the Commandant of the College, Major General Matthew Essien for the honour of inviting him and took the opportunity to congratulate all students and award winners.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lt Gen Blay expressed his delight for being invited as the Guest of Honour noting that, it had been 11 years since he retired from the Service, and felt privileged to be recognized.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1724071335.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1724071411.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1724071457.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He encouraged the students to take pride in being products of GAFCSC which he described as a place of opportunity, peace and inspiration that fosters self-discovery and propels individuals towards new horizons. He highlighted the importance of research as the cornerstone of the Ghana Armed Forces professional knowledge, emphasizing that it sharpens wisdom and positively influences one&rsquo;s environment.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He eulogized GAFCSC for its long-standing reputation as a Centre of Excellence, national pride and honour. He was particularly impressed by the College&rsquo;s recent development including the introduction of the PhD programme in Defence and International Politics, sets to begin in September 2024</p>', 1, '2024-08-19 12:44:37', '2024-08-19 12:48:32'),
(47, '1025c4cd-514f-4137-a60e-44f587541287', 'GAFCSC HOLDS RELIGIOUS SERVICE AHEAD OF GRADUATION CEREMONY', 'gafcsc-holds-religious-service-ahead-of-graduation-ceremony', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) as part of preparations for its upcoming Graduation Ceremony of the Senior Command and Staff Course (SCSC 45) and the Master of Science in Defence and International Politics (MDIP) Class of 2024 has held a religious graduation service on Sunday, 18 August, 2024 at Hamidu Hall in Teshie, &nbsp;Accra. </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The service was centered on the theme \"To whom much is given, much is expected\" (Luke 12:48). The sermon delivered by the Guest Preacher, Colonel (Col) John Kwamina Otoo (Rtd), a member of the National Peace Council, was not only inspiring but also edifying, resonating deeply with the congregation\'s sense of duty and spiritual responsibility. Col Otoo in his exhortation emphasized the vital role of obedience and trust in responding to God\'s call.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724182156.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">He stressed that while God bestows responsibilities, it is through obedience that one can truly fulfill the divine mandate. He encouraged the students to introspect on their ability to meet the expectations of those who have entrusted them with positions of authority.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The former Chief of Air Staff (CAS), Air Vice Marshal (AVM) Maxwell Manstebi-Tei Nagai (Rtd), who was the Guest of Honour,&nbsp; commended the students and staff of the College for their dedication, noting that the students had been thoroughly equipped with the knowledge required to excel both locally and internationally. He urged them to be worthy ambassadors of the College by exhibiting exemplary leadership and maintaining high standards in their future endeavours.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724182183.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The former CAS charged all and sundry to develop exceptional communication skills and a comprehensive understanding of the military and global affairs. He emphasized the importance of cooperation between the military and civil authorities, which he stated was crucial for effective governance and security.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724182272.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724182300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Awards were presented to some outstanding students of the MDIP Class of 2024. Mr Nuhu Alhassan Dicko secured the second position for Overall Best Student while Ms Alhassan Rabiatu Abisola took third place, while Mr Yaw Duodo and Mr Michael Kaamo Ayaim were recognized for their exceptional dissertations. The graduation ceremony for the SCSC 45 and MDIP Class of 2024 is set to take place on Friday, 23 August, 2024, at the GAFCSC.</span></p>', 1, '2024-08-20 19:31:52', '2024-08-20 19:33:28'),
(48, 'bdc74d98-3aed-4f9c-9cea-46510e58c55d', 'THE CHIEF COORD OF GAFCSC PROMOTED BRIG GEN', 'the-chief-coord-of-gafcsc-promoted-brig-gen', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">In a significant career milestone, the Chief Coordinator of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC), Col MO Mantey, has been promoted to the rank of Brigadier General. Consequently, he has been appointed as the Deputy Commandant of the Support Services Command, a role that recognizes his outstanding service and leadership in the Ghana Armed Forces.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724260236.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"653\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Additionally, other Officers in the College were also promoted in recognition of their dedication to duty. The Officers promoted from Lt Col to Col were Lt Col EL Odumang and Lt Col GK Mensah Yawson, while Maj Ivy Puplampu and Maj PS Hatse were elevated from Maj to Lt Col.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724260276.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"585\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724260361.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"700\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Commandant of GAFCSC, Major General Matthew Essien, congratulated Brig Gen Mantey and the other Senior Officers, for their hard work and significant contributions towards the development of the College. He expressed his confidence in their ability to excel in their new roles and wished the Officers success in future endeavors.</span></p>', 1, '2024-08-21 17:12:55', '2024-08-21 17:12:55'),
(49, '99bd85e0-c1ce-4d40-a176-0ea832ffc90d', 'VEEP CHARGES GAF TO UPHOLD TENETS OF PROFESSIONALISM FOR NATIONAL DEVELOPMENT', 'veep-charges-gaf-to-uphold-tenets-of-professionalism-for-national-development', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The Vice President of Ghana and Chairman of the Armed Forces Council, HE Alhaji Dr Mahamudu Bawumia has called on the graduating students of both the Senior Command and Staff Course 45 (SCSC 45) and the Defence and International Politics programme to maintain the highest standards of professionalism in the discharge of their duties. He underscored that the government\'s trust in the Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) is contingent on their unwavering integrity, dedication, and impartiality.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724450093.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The Vice President delivered this address to the Joint&nbsp; Graduation Ceremony for SCSC 45 and the Master of Science in International Politics (MDIP) Weekend Class of 2024 on Friday 23&nbsp;August 2024 in Teshie, Accra.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Dr Bawumia congratulated the graduating students and also highlighted GAF\'s esteemed reputation as one of Africa\'s premier&nbsp;Armed&nbsp;Forces, citing its significant contributions to global peace through United Nations operations. He attributed this&nbsp;reputation&nbsp;not only to the valour and performance of Ghanaian peacekeepers but also to the academic excellence fostered by the College.&nbsp;Acknowledging the evolving nature of&nbsp;global security threats, the Vice President emphasized the necessity of adapting to modern challenges.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">He praised the introduction of the Multi-Domain Operations Module in the College&rsquo;s curriculum, which equips graduates with the latest knowledge and skills for addressing contemporary security issues. He mentioned that the College has maintained a high standard of learning environment with requisite facilities in the face of numerous constraints to absorb the growing number of students.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The Commandant of the College, Major General Matthew Essien reported that the military component of the course had effectively prepared students to tackle&nbsp;the&nbsp;complex security&nbsp;issues facing Ghana, Africa and the world.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724450146.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">He announced the addition of a Master of Science in Security Studies to the College&rsquo;s academic offerings, as well as the upcoming launch of a PhD programme in Defence and International Politics next month. The Commandant further indicated that participants for this new programme would be expected from the military, sister security services, local government authorities, private sector, and media.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">The graduating course consisted of 98 students, 30 Allied students, and 36 MDIP students, all of whom completed nearly 12 months of intensive academic training. Awards were presented to outstanding students, with Maj E Kuudogrme recognized as the Honor Graduate. Maj Kuudogrme, Lt Cdr Osei Ananso, and Sqn Ldr Dawson-Ahmooah received the Service Awards.</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724450187.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1724450277.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"519\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Additional accolades included the Best Allied Student awarded to Sqn Ldr US Brown, the Most Improved Student to Maj SAF Apata, and the Everard Award to Maj M Osman. Maj EK Gamor was honoured as the Best MDIP Student, while Mr. Nuhu Alhassan Dicko earned the Overall Best MDIP Class of 2024 Award and the Best MDIP Dissertation Award.</p>', 1, '2024-08-23 22:00:29', '2024-08-23 22:07:10'),
(50, '98a75c89-8a13-49c9-9add-b1a2a27fa135', 'GTEC HOLDS CONFERENCE WITH GAFCSC', 'gtec-holds-conference-with-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>A three-member delegation from the Ghana Tertiary Education Commission (GTEC), led by Dr Osei Kuffour held a conference with the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Wednesday, <span lang=\"EN-US\">11 September </span>2024, at Teshie.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The <span lang=\"EN-US\">Conference was</span> aimed to evaluate the readiness of the GAFCSC <span lang=\"EN-US\">J</span>unior <span lang=\"EN-US\">D</span>ivision for <span lang=\"EN-US\">the accreditation of a Post Graduate Diploma in Military Science, Security and Defence. The programme is aimed at enhancing the academic and professional capabilities of military officers and other security sector professionals.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1726169867.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Dean of the <span lang=\"EN-US\">College, Dr </span>Vladimir Antwi Danso said the program<span lang=\"EN-US\">me</span> is designed to equip <span lang=\"EN-US\">both military officers </span>and civilians <span lang=\"EN-US\">at the junior and middle - level management </span>with <span lang=\"EN-US\">the necessary skills i</span>n command and leadership roles. He added that <span lang=\"EN-US\">admission to </span>the program<span lang=\"EN-US\">me</span> is not limited <span lang=\"EN-US\">to only military officers but also to personnel of sister security services and individuals in the security sector</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1726169931.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dr Osei Kuffour commended <span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;GAFCSC </span>&nbsp;for <span lang=\"EN-US\">its </span>&nbsp;remarkable work <span lang=\"EN-US\">as a Centre of Excellence for training future commanders and leaders in defence and international politics. He stated&nbsp; that, with the introduction of this post graduate diploma, GAFCSC will contribute to the professional development of Ghana\'s security landscape.</span></p>', 1, '2024-09-12 19:39:16', '2024-09-12 19:44:18'),
(51, '597f45df-7ebc-4257-a1d5-90ab9002504e', 'SENIOR COMMAND COURSE 45 DONATES TO GAFCSC', 'senior-command-course-45-donates-to-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Alumni of Senior Command and Staff Course 45 has donated a lectern and wireless microphones to the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Friday, 13th September 2024, at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">S</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">enior </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">S</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">tudent, Lieutenant Colonel AK Effah, on behalf of the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ourse expressed appreciation to the Commandant, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ourse </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">I</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">nstructors, and the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ollege </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">S</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">taff for their support in enhancing their knowledge and skills during the program</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">me</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">. He acknowledged the Commandant&rsquo;s constant presence </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">and guidance </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">throughout the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Course </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">and his keen eye for quality and aesthetics.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1726313120.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Commandant of the College, Major General&nbsp; Matthew Essien expressed his heartfelt gratitude to the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ourse for their thoughtful and generous gesture. He noted that the donation was unexpected but would significantly enhance the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ollege\'s equipment and infrastructure.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Maj Gen Essien emphasized that GAFCSC is the only college at the operational level, and their contribution would greatly benefit the institution. He praised the course members for their efforts and assured them that the </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">C</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">ollege would value and cherish the gift for years to </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">come.</span></span></p>', 1, '2024-09-14 11:25:38', '2024-09-14 11:28:53');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `uuid`, `title`, `slug`, `sub_title`, `published_by`, `category`, `content`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(52, '6ea8b4c3-36a4-42d3-85f7-3cd2f109cfbd', 'GAFCSC ORGANIZES SEND OFF PARTY FOR NSP', 'gafcsc-organizes-send-off-party-for-nsp', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College(GAFCSC) has organized a send-off party for the National Service Personnel 2023/2024 year group on Friday 27 September 2024 at the College&rsquo;s Canteen.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The purpose of the programme was to celebrate and appreciate the personnel&rsquo;s efforts, contributions, and dedication added up to the college\'s manpower to effectively execute their duties.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727727869.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"750\" /></span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Guest of Honour and the Chief Coordinator of&nbsp; GAFCSC, Colonel (Col) William Archibold Kwabiah in his address congratulated the personnel on their service and contribution towards the effectiveness of the college manpower.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">He mentioned that the college has taken note of most of their concerns raised on the availability of vehicles for personnel in the submission of their assessment forms amongst others.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727727913.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"750\" /></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Col Kwabiah advised NSPs to take their health seriously, be self-disciplined, adopt patience, and learn from others\' experiences. He thanked them on behalf of the Commandant Major General (Maj Gen) Matthew Essien and urged them to keep the bond formed between them and the college as well as the Ghana Armed Forces as a whole.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727727947.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" /></span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Chief Instructor Joint Studies, Colonel Daniel Agbekor mentioned that knowledge and experience are never useless because they help shape every individual. He advised personnel to be confident and also cultivate the habits of saving for the future.</span></p>', 1, '2024-09-30 20:26:06', '2024-09-30 20:31:29'),
(53, 'c313bf78-8348-4462-8860-7a8773154b4a', 'GAFCSC MATRICULATES SENIOR COMMAND COURSE 46', 'gafcsc-matriculates-senior-command-course-46', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has held a matriculation ceremony for Senior Command and Staff Course 46 on Wednesday, 1 October 2024, at Teshie.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727965887.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In his welcome address to students and invited guests, The Commandant of the College, Major General Matthew Essien revealed that the ceremony represents a significant milestone in their academic and professional development. He emphasized that the challenging academic path they are embarking on is essential for shaping the future of national and global security.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727965928.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Maj Gen Essien stated that gaining mastery of the subjects would equip students with the analytical skills and strategic insights necessary to handle complex challenges. He encouraged them to seize the opportunity with enthusiasm, engage actively in their studies, participate in discussions, and push themselves to think beyond conventional limits.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727965957.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The Guest of Honour, who doubles as a representative of the Rector of </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> (GIMPA) Dr Patrick Tandoh-Offin, emphasized the importance of matriculation ceremonies as the formal entry point for students into higher education.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><img src=\"../../uploads/1727965981.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; line-height: 22px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 24px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Dr Patrick Tandoh underscored the potential benefits of the partnership between GIMPA and GAFCSC, aiming to fulfill their commitments and establish a center of excellence. He urged them to seek knowledge, becoming well-informed and well-rounded individuals who can positively impact their communities and society. &nbsp;</span></p>', 1, '2024-10-03 14:33:09', '2024-10-03 14:33:09'),
(54, '23ec1cbf-55a3-49f1-92bf-72e1135a2271', 'GAFCSC HOLDS INDUCTION RELIGIOUS PARADE', 'gafcsc-holds-induction-religious-parade', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) has held its induction religious parade for Senior Command and Staff Course 46 at Hamidu Hall on Sunday, 6th October 2024, Teshie.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>During his sermon on &ldquo;Enhancing Professionalism through Knowledge Acquisition,&rdquo; Colonel Peter Nyarko Duodu encouraged participants to pursue knowledge diligently to bolster their professionalism.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1728343543.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He emphasized that acquiring knowledge requires adherence to the institution&rsquo;s standards and ethics, as professionalism establishes trust and credibility. He added that professionalism also leads to personal satisfaction, and&nbsp;self-respect, which boosts self-esteem.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In his address, the Guest of Honor for the ceremony Rear Admiral Peter Faido (Rtd) expressed heartfelt gratitude to the Commandant of the College, Major General Matthew Essien, and the staff for their hospitality. He emphasized that military professionalism extends beyond merely wearing the uniform; it encompasses upholding the highest standards of integrity, respect, discipline, and leadership.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1728343609.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>He stressed that knowledge is not merely an asset but a necessity, and without ongoing learning, one risks falling behind. Rear Admiral Peter (Rtd) urged participants to take the course seriously, reminding them that the nation&rsquo;s defense lies with them. He added that the knowledge they acquire will strengthen their capacity to make informed decisions and demonstrate sound judgment and strategic foresight.</p>', 1, '2024-10-07 23:27:09', '2024-10-07 23:29:23'),
(55, '98c4840f-d28f-4e51-9eb2-75a7bef42e0c', 'THE COMMANDANT OF GHANA NATIONAL FIRE SERVICE PAYS A COURTESY CALL ON COMMANDANT', 'the-commandant-of-ghana-national-fire-service-pays-a-courtesy-call-on-commandant', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>A two-member delegation from the Ghana National Fire Service College, led by Deputy Chief Officer and Commandant of the Fire Service College, James Ankrah, along with Assistant Chief Fire Officer Dr. Gerald Acheampong, Director of Studies, has paid a courtesy call on the Commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Command and Staff College (GAFCSC) on Wednesday, October 9, 2024 at Teshie</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The purpose of the visit was to acquire knowledge and insights to help design a structure and academic framework for the establishment of the Fire Service College, with the intention of replicating a similar model for the Fire Service.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1728900283.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The delegation was welcomed by the Deputy Commandant of GAFCSC, Brigadier General Albert Dawohoso, on behalf of the College&rsquo;s Commandant, Major General Matthew Essien. They were given an overview of the college&rsquo;s organizational structure, operations, and administration.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../../uploads/1728900419.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1728900312.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"665\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;The team expressed their enthusiasm for the visit and indicated that they plan to make regular visits to gain further insight into the college&rsquo;s work.</p>', 1, '2024-10-14 10:05:32', '2024-10-22 12:07:55'),
(56, 'd6810274-a51e-4e8c-9729-5f98a773c883', 'VISIT OF THE CHIEF OF THE ARMY STAFF TO GAFCSC', 'visit-of-the-chief-of-the-army-staff-to-gafcsc', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">On Thursday, 17 October 2024, the Chief of the Army Staff, (COAS), Major General Bismarck Kwasi Onwona visited the College, delivered a lecture on his vision for the Ghana Army and interacted with students of Senior Command and Staff Course 46 at the Hamidu Hall. The COAS was accompanied by some principal staff officers from the Army Headquarters who supported the COAS in delivering his vision to the students. The visit of the COAS to the College was part of activities slated to mark the Army Combat Power Week which is very salient on the students&rsquo; academic calendar.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">During the COAS presentation to the students, he stated that his vision for the Ghana Army, was to &ldquo;<strong>Keep the Army as a part of the Ghana Armed Forces as a cohesive, motivated and well-rounded force in order to execute its roles and responsibilities professionally in protecting the territorial integrity of Ghana</strong>&rdquo;. He added that the Ghana Army\'s roles and mission are accompanied by a strategic plan for accomplishing its goals.&nbsp; He continued that plan were far advanced and in motion to provide effective training, administration and welfare packages for the entire Army personnel at all levels.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">During the interaction session of the COAS visit, he highlighted that, there was the need for effective training for all personnel which will result in reinforcing the professionalism and dedication imbibed in our future military leaders as they discharge of their respective duties. He further acknowledged the salient role of GAFCSC in shaping the knowledge of such capable officers for national security challenges. He entreated the students to seize the opportunity provided by the College, learn as much as they could and use the knowledge gained to mould their career paths in their respective Armed Forces.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">The COAS concluded his visit to the College by presenting an undisclosed amount of cash donation to support the College\'s infrastructural developments. The Commandant, Staff and Students of the College were very grateful to the COAS for his memorious visit to the College.</span></p>', 1, '2024-10-30 07:54:35', '2024-10-30 07:55:51'),
(57, '9a303258-24fe-4f4b-bf02-f7866d2d81d0', 'COURSE 46 CLIMAXES SERVICE WEEK CELEBRATIONS WITH LAND COMBAT AND FIRE POWER DEMONSTRATION', 'course-46-climaxes-service-week-celebrations-with-land-combat-and-fire-power-demonstration', NULL, 'ADMIN', NULL, '<p>The Ghana Armed Forces (GAF) exhibited its military strength and capabilities during the Land Combat and Firepower Demonstration held at the Bundase Training Camp.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The exercise, conducted on Friday 1 November 2024, had the 2 Infantry Battalion as the lead unit, with support from various battalions and regiments. Sea and air strategies were provided the Ghana Navy and the Air Force. The exercise served as a practical platform for students of the Senior Command and Staff Course 46 to employ Joint Task Force battle groups in deep, close, and rear operations.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1730927252.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guest of Honour, the Chief of the Air Staff (CAS), Air Vice Marshal (AVM) Frederick Asare Bekoe, described the exercise as essential for the career development of students, with a particular focus on operational concepts and capabilities.</p>\n<p>AVM Bekoe encouraged&nbsp; personnel to uphold their constitutional duties in national defence and emphasised the importance of such exercises in ensuring GAF&rsquo;s readiness to neutralise and counter insurgencies.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../uploads/1730927324.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The CAS commended GAF for its internal security initiatives, including Operations Halt, Boafo, Ahodwo, and Calm Life, aimed at preserving peace and stability. He also urged the public to support Ghana&rsquo;s democratic status and remain vigilant against unpatriotic activities.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><img src=\"../../uploads/1730927370.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" /></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Brigadier General Samuel Yeboah Asare, the General Officer Commanding Southern Command, reiterated the GAF\'s constitutional mandate to defend the territorial integrity of the country and assist civil authorities to maintain internal security. He underlined that the Ghana Army regularly undergoes training to improve its abilities, strategies, and preparedness for new challenges as the primary force in land-based operations. According to him, the Navy and Air Force provided crucial support during the demonstration, which depicted a successful blockade of a fictitious invading force.</p>', 1, '2024-11-06 21:09:41', '2024-11-06 21:10:41');

